main event: A civilian engineer spotted a white, star-like object in the sky near Orlando, Florida on May 25, 1960.
interesting points: The object was first seen at 45 degrees above the horizon, descended to 24 degrees, and then disappeared at 40 degrees above the horizon.
The object moved in a generally southeast to northwest direction, holding a steady course.
The sighting lasted for approximately 2 minutes.
The observer could not determine the size of the object due to its distance.
The report suggests the object may have been an artificial satellite, but also mentions it could have been a high-flying aircraft.
